annotationA: Lysophospholipid acyltransferase 5; Acyltransferase which mediates the conversion of lysophosphatidylcholine (1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine or LPC) to phosphatidylcholine (1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3- phosphocholine or PC) (LPCAT activity). annotationB: CG4825, isoform A; CDP-diacylglycerol-serine O-phosphatidyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: phosphatidylserine biosynthetic process; neurogenesis
